AI Voice Agent

A Python-based voice assistant that listens to your voice, converts speech to text, generates a GPT response, and speaks back in real time.

Features
    Live voice recording and transcription using OpenAI Whisper.
	GPT responses via gpt-4o-mini.
	Text-to-speech output with OpenAI TTS (tts-1).
	Simple memory system to remember recent conversation.
	Continuous listening mode — speak anytime; say “stop” to exit.
	Fully GitHub-safe (API key stored in environment variable).

Requirements
    Python 3.10+
    Packages:
pip install openai sounddevice soundfile numpy

Setup
A   Get an OpenAI secret key starting with sk-…
	Go to OpenAI API Keys￼
	Add a payment method if required.
B   Set environment variable:
    Windows CMD:
    set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
C   Run the agent:
    python voice_agent.py
Usage
	Speak clearly into your microphone when prompted.
	The agent will print what you said and the assistant’s reply.
	You will also hear the assistant’s response via speakers.
	Say “stop” to exit the program.

